<paragraph id="AF78DC38FFBEDF164B97A3ACFDF3EF18" blockId="11.[211,1172,887,1525]" pageId="11" pageNumber="2745">
Morphological examination of the 
<typeStatus id="707C629AFFBEDF164928A3ACFD30E8F9" box="[620,720,927,951]" pageId="11" pageNumber="2745">holotype</typeStatus>
of 
<taxonomicName id="68C7A7BBFFBEDF1649B8A3ACFC68E8F9" box="[764,904,927,951]" class="Insecta" family="Andrenidae" genus="Arhysosage" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="11" pageNumber="2745" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="cactorum">
<emphasis id="9DB3002AFFBEDF1649B8A3ACFC68E8F9" box="[764,904,927,951]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="2745">A. cactorum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(
<figureCitation id="37FCC0BDFFBEDF1648DFA3ACFBB6E8F9" box="[923,1110,927,951]" captionStart="Figure 4" captionStartId="7.[211,278,1300,1322]" captionTargetBox="[214,1170,167,1267]" captionTargetId="figure-5@7.[213,1170,167,1267]" captionTargetPageId="7" captionText="Figure 4. Arhysosage cactorum Moure. (A) Female, head in frontal view; (B) holotype male, head in frontal view; (C) female, lateral habitus; (D) male holotype, lateral habitus; (E) male holotype, dorsal view; (F) male holotype, mesosoma in dorsal view. Scale bar 1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5197977" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5197977/files/figure.png" pageId="11" pageNumber="2745">Figure 4B, D–F</figureCitation>
) and 
<taxonomicName id="68C7A7BBFFBEDF164B97A38CFE73E899" authorityName="Moure" authorityYear="1999" box="[211,403,959,983]" class="Insecta" family="Andrenidae" genus="Arhysosage" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="11" pageNumber="2745" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="melanothricha">
<emphasis id="9DB3002AFFBEDF164B97A38CFE73E899" box="[211,403,959,983]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="2745">A. melanothricha</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(
<figureCitation id="37FCC0BDFFBEDF164AE2A38DFDA5E898" box="[422,581,958,982]" captionStart="Figure 6" captionStartId="12.[143,210,1286,1308]" captionTargetBox="[145,1102,170,1253]" captionTargetId="figure-3@12.[145,1102,169,1253]" captionTargetPageId="12" captionText="Figure 6. Arhysosage melanothricha Moure, male holotype. (A) Head in frontal view; (B) lateral habitus; (C) mesosoma in dorsal view; (D) hind tibia, detail of basitibial plate; (E) metasoma in dorsal view; (F) pygidial plate. Scale bar 1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5197981" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5197981/files/figure.png" pageId="11" pageNumber="2745">Figures 6A–F</figureCitation>
) supports the status of 
<taxonomicName id="68C7A7BBFFBEDF16481FA38CFBFBE899" authorityName="Moure" authorityYear="1999" box="[859,1051,959,983]" class="Insecta" family="Andrenidae" genus="Arhysosage" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="11" pageNumber="2745" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="melanothricha">
<emphasis id="9DB3002AFFBEDF16481FA38CFBFBE899" box="[859,1051,959,983]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="2745">A. melanothricha</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
as a valid species, as initially proposed by 
<bibRefCitation id="CB56A1C9FFBEDF164976A3ECFD2BE8B8" author="Moure JS" box="[562,715,990,1014]" pageId="11" pageNumber="2745" pagination="241 - 247" refId="ref5545" refString="Moure JS. 1999. Duas especies novas de Arhysosage Brethes do Brasil (Rio Grande do Sul) e da Argentina (Salta) (Hymenoptera, Apoidea, Panurginae). Rev Bras Zool. 16: 241 - 247." type="journal article" year="1999">Moure (1999)</bibRefCitation>
and subsequently by 
<bibRefCitation id="CB56A1C9FFBEDF1648FCA3ECFB6EE8B8" author="Moure JS &amp; Urban D &amp; Melo GAR" box="[952,1166,990,1014]" pageId="11" pageNumber="2745" refId="ref5588" refString="Moure JS, Urban D, Melo GAR. 2007. Catalogue of bees (Hymenoptera, Apoidea) in the Neotropical Region. Curitiba (BR): Sociedade Brasileira de Entomologia." type="book" year="2007">Moure et al. (2007)</bibRefCitation>
. In the description of 
<taxonomicName id="68C7A7BBFFBEDF164AFAA3CDFD9BEF58" authorityName="Moure" authorityYear="1999" box="[446,635,1022,1046]" class="Insecta" family="Andrenidae" genus="Arhysosage" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="11" pageNumber="2745" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="melanothricha">
<emphasis id="9DB3002AFFBEDF164AFAA3CDFD9BEF58" box="[446,635,1022,1046]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="2745">A. melanothricha</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, the legends of figures are switched. The correct association of 
<bibRefCitation id="CB56A1C9FFBEDF164A38A42DFDCCEF78" author="Moure JS" box="[380,556,1054,1078]" pageId="11" pageNumber="2745" pagination="241 - 247" refId="ref5545" refString="Moure JS. 1999. Duas especies novas de Arhysosage Brethes do Brasil (Rio Grande do Sul) e da Argentina (Salta) (Hymenoptera, Apoidea, Panurginae). Rev Bras Zool. 16: 241 - 247." type="journal article" year="1999">Moure’s (1999)</bibRefCitation>
figures is: fig. 1 illustrates 
<taxonomicName id="68C7A7BBFFBEDF16482CA42DFBC8EF78" authorityName="Moure" authorityYear="1999" box="[872,1064,1054,1078]" class="Insecta" family="Andrenidae" genus="Arhysosage" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="11" pageNumber="2745" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="melanothricha">
<emphasis id="9DB3002AFFBEDF16482CA42DFBC8EF78" box="[872,1064,1054,1078]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="2745">A. melanothricha</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, whereas fig. 2 illustrates 
<taxonomicName id="68C7A7BBFFBEDF164AC0A40DFDECEF18" box="[388,524,1086,1110]" class="Insecta" family="Andrenidae" genus="Arhysosage" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="11" pageNumber="2745" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="cactorum">
<emphasis id="9DB3002AFFBEDF164AC0A40DFDECEF18" box="[388,524,1086,1110]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="2745">A. cactorum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="AF78DC38FFBEDF164BBAA46DFCCBEEBB" blockId="11.[211,1172,887,1525]" pageId="11" pageNumber="2745">
<taxonomicName id="68C7A7BBFFBEDF164BBAA46DFDC0EF38" authorityName="Moure" authorityYear="1999" box="[254,544,1118,1142]" class="Insecta" family="Andrenidae" genus="Arhysosage" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="11" pageNumber="2745" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="melanothricha">
<emphasis id="9DB3002AFFBEDF164BBAA46DFDC0EF38" box="[254,544,1118,1142]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="2745">Arhysosage melanothricha</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is known from a single male 
<typeStatus id="707C629AFFBEDF16482AA46DFC34EF38" box="[878,980,1118,1142]" pageId="11" pageNumber="2745">holotype</typeStatus>
. As described by 
<bibRefCitation id="CB56A1C9FFBEDF164B97A44CFE90EFD8" author="Moure JS" box="[211,368,1150,1174]" pageId="11" pageNumber="2745" pagination="241 - 247" refId="ref5545" refString="Moure JS. 1999. Duas especies novas de Arhysosage Brethes do Brasil (Rio Grande do Sul) e da Argentina (Salta) (Hymenoptera, Apoidea, Panurginae). Rev Bras Zool. 16: 241 - 247." type="journal article" year="1999">Moure (1999)</bibRefCitation>
, 
<taxonomicName id="68C7A7BBFFBEDF164A3AA44DFDDCEFD8" authorityName="Moure" authorityYear="1999" box="[382,572,1150,1174]" class="Insecta" family="Andrenidae" genus="Arhysosage" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="11" pageNumber="2745" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="melanothricha">
<emphasis id="9DB3002AFFBEDF164A3AA44DFDDCEFD8" box="[382,572,1150,1174]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="2745">A. melanothricha</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
can be readily distinguished by its long dark pilosity on the head and mesoscutum, which contrasts with the yellow body (
<figureCitation id="37FCC0BDFFBEDF1648AAA4ADFB67EFF8" box="[1006,1159,1182,1206]" captionStart="Figure 6" captionStartId="12.[143,210,1286,1308]" captionTargetBox="[145,1102,170,1253]" captionTargetId="figure-3@12.[145,1102,169,1253]" captionTargetPageId="12" captionText="Figure 6. Arhysosage melanothricha Moure, male holotype. (A) Head in frontal view; (B) lateral habitus; (C) mesosoma in dorsal view; (D) hind tibia, detail of basitibial plate; (E) metasoma in dorsal view; (F) pygidial plate. Scale bar 1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5197981" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5197981/files/figure.png" pageId="11" pageNumber="2745">Figure 6A–C</figureCitation>
). 
<taxonomicName id="68C7A7BBFFBEDF164B97A48DFE13EF98" authorityName="Moure" authorityYear="1999" box="[211,499,1214,1238]" class="Insecta" family="Andrenidae" genus="Arhysosage" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="11" pageNumber="2745" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="melanothricha">
<emphasis id="9DB3002AFFBEDF164B97A48DFE13EF98" box="[211,499,1214,1238]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="2745">Arhysosage melanothricha</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is morphologically similar to 
<taxonomicName id="68C7A7BBFFBEDF164878A48DFC2DEF98" box="[828,973,1214,1238]" class="Insecta" family="Andrenidae" genus="Arhysosage" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="11" pageNumber="2745" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="atronulata">
<emphasis id="9DB3002AFFBEDF164878A48DFC2DEF98" box="[828,973,1214,1238]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="2745">A. atronulata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName id="68C7A7BBFFBEDF16489EA48DFB83EF98" baseAuthorityName="Friese" baseAuthorityYear="1908" box="[986,1123,1214,1238]" class="Insecta" family="Andrenidae" genus="Arhysosage" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="11" pageNumber="2745" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="bifasciata">
<emphasis id="9DB3002AFFBEDF16489EA48DFB83EF98" box="[986,1123,1214,1238]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="2745">A. bifasciata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName id="68C7A7BBFFBEDF164B97A4EDFEB6EFB8" baseAuthorityName="Friese" baseAuthorityYear="1908" box="[211,342,1246,1270]" class="Insecta" family="Andrenidae" genus="Arhysosage" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="11" pageNumber="2745" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="ochracea">
<emphasis id="9DB3002AFFBEDF164B97A4EDFEB6EFB8" box="[211,342,1246,1270]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="2745">A. ochracea</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
due to the presence of yellow bands on the metasomal terga (
<figureCitation id="37FCC0BDFFBEDF164F56A4EEFB63EFBB" box="[1042,1155,1245,1269]" captionStart="Figure 6" captionStartId="12.[143,210,1286,1308]" captionTargetBox="[145,1102,170,1253]" captionTargetId="figure-3@12.[145,1102,169,1253]" captionTargetPageId="12" captionText="Figure 6. Arhysosage melanothricha Moure, male holotype. (A) Head in frontal view; (B) lateral habitus; (C) mesosoma in dorsal view; (D) hind tibia, detail of basitibial plate; (E) metasoma in dorsal view; (F) pygidial plate. Scale bar 1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5197981" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5197981/files/figure.png" pageId="11" pageNumber="2745">Figure 6E</figureCitation>
), and the distal margin of male clypeus is slightly convex between the lateral corners (
<figureCitation id="37FCC0BDFFBEDF164A52A52EFE6DEE7B" box="[278,397,1309,1333]" captionStart="Figure 1" captionStartId="4.[143,210,1629,1651]" captionTargetBox="[162,1084,161,1596]" captionTargetId="figure-3@4.[162,1085,161,1596]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="Figure 1. Arhysosage biguttulata sp. nov. (A) Female holotype, head in frontal view; (B) male paratype, head in frontal view; (C) female holotype, lateral habitus; (D) male paratype, lateral habitus; (E) female, mesosoma in dorsal view; (F) male, mesosoma in dorsal view; (G) male hind tibia, basitibial plate in detail; (H) female metasoma, pygidial plate in detail. Scale bar 0.5 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5197969" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5197969/files/figure.png" pageId="11" pageNumber="2745">Figure 1A</figureCitation>
). In Engel’s key (
<bibRefCitation id="CB56A1C9FFBEDF164926A52EFD04EE7B" author="Engel MS" box="[610,740,1309,1333]" pageId="11" pageNumber="2745" pagination="182 - 208" refId="ref5427" refString="Engel MS. 2000. A revision of the panurgine bee genus Arhysosage (Hymenoptera: Andrenidae). J Hym Res. 9: 182 - 208." type="journal article" year="2000">Engel 2000</bibRefCitation>
), this species runs to couplet 6 with 
<taxonomicName id="68C7A7BBFFBEDF164B97A50EFE82EE1B" box="[211,354,1341,1365]" class="Insecta" family="Andrenidae" genus="Arhysosage" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="11" pageNumber="2745" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="ochraceae">
<emphasis id="9DB3002AFFBEDF164B97A50EFE82EE1B" box="[211,354,1341,1365]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="2745">A. ochraceae</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName id="68C7A7BBFFBEDF164AD8A50EFDC7EE1B" baseAuthorityName="Friese" baseAuthorityYear="1908" box="[412,551,1341,1365]" class="Insecta" family="Andrenidae" genus="Arhysosage" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="11" pageNumber="2745" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="bifasciata">
<emphasis id="9DB3002AFFBEDF164AD8A50EFDC7EE1B" box="[412,551,1341,1365]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="2745">A. bifasciata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
due to the following: presence of a predominantly yellow face, with black marks restricted to facial foveae (
<figureCitation id="37FCC0BDFFBEDF164867A56EFC75EE3B" box="[803,917,1373,1397]" captionStart="Figure 6" captionStartId="12.[143,210,1286,1308]" captionTargetBox="[145,1102,170,1253]" captionTargetId="figure-3@12.[145,1102,169,1253]" captionTargetPageId="12" captionText="Figure 6. Arhysosage melanothricha Moure, male holotype. (A) Head in frontal view; (B) lateral habitus; (C) mesosoma in dorsal view; (D) hind tibia, detail of basitibial plate; (E) metasoma in dorsal view; (F) pygidial plate. Scale bar 1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5197981" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5197981/files/figure.png" pageId="11" pageNumber="2745">Figure 6A</figureCitation>
), yellow scape, clypeus with coarse and rounded punctures, clypeus with dense pubescence at apicolateral margins, and pygidial plate apex weakly emarginate (
<figureCitation id="37FCC0BDFFBEDF1649BDA5AEFC89EEFB" box="[761,873,1437,1461]" captionStart="Figure 6" captionStartId="12.[143,210,1286,1308]" captionTargetBox="[145,1102,170,1253]" captionTargetId="figure-3@12.[145,1102,169,1253]" captionTargetPageId="12" captionText="Figure 6. Arhysosage melanothricha Moure, male holotype. (A) Head in frontal view; (B) lateral habitus; (C) mesosoma in dorsal view; (D) hind tibia, detail of basitibial plate; (E) metasoma in dorsal view; (F) pygidial plate. Scale bar 1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5197981" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5197981/files/figure.png" pageId="11" pageNumber="2745">Figure 6F</figureCitation>
). However, in couplet 4 of the same key, the correct sentence would be “dense pubescence at apicolateral margins of clypeus and clypeus with coarse round punctures”.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
